Text: Hi Teacher2,I fell a bit short on my goals for the week.
We had a meeting with Jeramiah on Wednesday afternoon and had planned out to sort out the overlapping box thing along with a few others but we didn't make it.
We have since fixed some things including the overlapping box but still since we didn't get it done for the final presentation it was a bit of a shame.
The problem with it was down to just basic mistakes like using the wrong types to compare in the if statements about whether the coordinates from the region in the bounding box were there.
It was good that Koko was able to get the JSON thing going and Nene and Rara added to the prepossessing part.
Next time I'd probably ask to have a meeting with the team sooner and see if anyone could figure what was wrong.
I spent quite a bit of time but I did learn a lot just thinking it through for many hours.
Eventually the solution was pretty easy but I'm glad I spent the time to really understand what was going on.
I am pretty satisfied with the presentation and the application in general but I would like to have been able to complete it properly.
I feel like I have invested enough time into to understand how its working now so it might be worth working on it a little bit before the internship.
Hopefully I can add some of the final features and format it well for delivery and in the process gain a few extra skills.
I don't think anyone else is that keen on that but I will let them know incase they wanted to help.
Thanks a lot for the help and mentorship over the year.
It was great fun and I have learned a lot.
It is funny to think at the start of the year I knew almost nothing at all about software development.
I think the program is really good and you guys do a great job so the SHIFT programme (or future equivalent) will come highly recommended from me.
